                <h3>Narrow list of QTL </h3>
                <p>To initiate the tool, click on the &#147Narrow QTLs&#148 button. If the tool started narrowing
		successfully a processing dialog box will appear, which will give the current state of the 
		narrowing process. The dialog box is modal, and will not disappear until the analysis is 
		done. You are still able to use your browser, but selecting another tab, or opening another 
		window but the specific tab the analysis is running in will be blocked until the narrowing 
		is completed.</p>

                <p>The time required to narrow a QTL list depends of the number of QTLs and the overlap
		between QTLs.</p>

                <p>If the narrowing does not start a dialog box will appear letting you know the error.
		Please correct the error and click &#147Narrow QTLs&#148 again.</p>

                <p>You have also the option to upload a new QTL list after clearing the QTL list table by
		clicking the &#147Clear&#148 button.</p>

                <h2>Additional functionality of the QNT for future releases</h2>
                <p>Some of the functionality of the tool is not yet implemented for the current alpha-release.
	We currently work on the following additions to the QNT:
                <ul>
                    <li>Major additions:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Adding support for Strain synonyms: The user will have the option to use well
					known/used synonyms of strains. For example, if someone would enter"B6" we will assume 
					the user means C57BL/6J. The user will still have the option to edit incorect spelling 
					as currently available.</li>
                            <li>Adding phenotype search to obtain a QTL lists from MGI: In the furture the user will have
					the option to assable a QTL list by way of searching the currently published QTL available
					online.</li>
                            <li>Adding options to download the result files (excel or tab delimited reports): In the
					future the user will have the option to download all result files for further modifications
					or analysis steps.</li>
                            <li>Add Cross Species functionality: In the future the user will be able to use evidence
					from multiple species by integrating the functionality of cross-species conversion. </li>
                            <li>Add user provided microarray experiments and support for more micoarray platforms:
					In the future we will provide the opportunity to upload microarray experiments. Also, we
					anticipate to support more than the currently available two affymetrix platforms.</li>
                            <li>Add GWAS support: We will implement the function to include genome-wide association
					mapping results (and possibly analyses if strain survey data are provided) from the mouse.</li>
                            <li>Enhance liver/Shockley data to break out by gender as well:</li>
                            <li>Add threading to back end and perform analysis by chromosome to improve performance
					(meaning multiple chromosomes for one analysis could run at the same time).  This may 
					require a bigger server but should improve performance on processing of data with many chromosomes.</li>	
                        </ul>
                    </li><br>
                    <li>Minor additions:
                        <ul>
                            <li>For GEX radio buttons, make &#147options&#148 only appear if the user selects that radio
					button:</li>
                            <li>Fix width/height/message of processing dialog.</li>
                            <li>Add an option to exclude snp annotation types from the result.</li>
                            <li>Include Gene Start and End position in the gene table.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
	We would appreciate any additional suggestions to improve the efficiency and the functionality of the 
	QNT.</p>

